DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
);
 
TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$p = random(3,8,1);
$q = random(2,($p-1),1);
$k = random(2,5,1);

$p1 = $p+1;
$q1 = $q+1;
$kq1 = $k*$q1;

BEGIN_TEXT

Find an antiderivative \(P(t)\) of 
\( p(t)=t^{$p}-\frac{t^{$q}}{$k} - t \)

$PAR
\(P(t) = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp( "(1/$p1)*t^{$p1} - (1/$kq1)*t^{$q1} - (1/2)*t^2", 'var'=>['t'], 
	      'mode'=>'antider' ) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We note that \(p(t) = t^{$p} - {1\over$k} t^{$q} - t\), so 
\(P(t)\) must have the form 
\(P(t) = \frac{t^{$p1}}{$p1}-\frac{t^{$q1}}{$kq1} - \frac{t^2}{2}\), 
plus any constant value. 

END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
